  "prompt": "Is money laundering a contravention of legal standards?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a contravention of legal standards. It is a crime in virtually every country in the world.\n\nHere's why and what laws it contravenes:\n\n*   **What it is:** Money laundering is the process of disguising the origins of illegally obtained money so that it appears to come from a legitimate source.\n\n*   **Why it's illegal:** It allows criminals to profit from their illegal activities without detection and prosecution. It also undermines the integrity of financial institutions and the economy as a whole.\n\n*   **Laws it contravenes:**\n    *   **Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws:** These are the primary laws specifically designed to combat money laundering. They typically include provisions that:\n        *   Make it illegal to engage in money laundering activities (e.g., concealing the source of funds, transferring illicit funds).\n        *   Require financial institutions to implement Know Your Customer (KYC) and Customer Due Diligence (CDD) measures.\n        *   Mandate the reporting of suspicious transactions (Suspicious Activity Reports or SARs).\n        *   Impose penalties for non-compliance.\n    *   **Laws related to the underlying criminal activity (Predicate Offenses):** Money laundering is almost always linked to an underlying crime that generated the illicit funds. These underlying crimes are called \"predicate offenses.\" Examples include:\n        *   Drug trafficking\n        *   Fraud\n        *   Corruption\n        *   Theft\n        *   Extortion\n        *   Tax evasion\n        *   Human trafficking\n        *   Terrorism financing\n\n*   **International Standards:** The Financial Action Task Force (FATF) is an inter-governmental body that sets international standards to combat money laundering and terrorist financing. Many countries adopt these standards into their national laws.\n\nIn summary, money laundering is a direct violation of laws designed to prevent it and is indirectly linked to violations of laws related to the crimes that generate the dirty money in the first place.\n",
